Taiwanese actress and model

Lene Lai (Chinese: 賴琳恩; pinyin: Lài Lín'ēn; born 6 June 1989) is a Taiwanese actress and model. She was the 2nd runner-up of the Miss Asia Pageant 2008.[1][2][3][4][5]

Life and career

[edit]

Lai studied at Tainan University of Technology, but she has since put her study on hold.[citation needed]

She participated in the television program Everybody Speaks Nonsenses II - Hot Pot. In 2006, she joined the variety show Blackie's Teenage Club [zh].[6] She has played small roles in television series My Queen and Bull Fighting.[citation needed]

Lai became the second Taiwanese to win a title from the Miss Asia Pageant.[citation needed] After winning the pageant, she was signed by Asia Television as an actress in 2009.[7]

Lai is married to singer and actor Nylon Chen.[8]
